  "id": "Bernard Arnault & family",
  "description": "Bernard Jean Étienne Arnault (born 5 March 1949) is a French businessperson, investor, and art collector. He is the founder, chairman, and CEO of LVMH Moët Hennessy Louis Vuitton, the world's largest luxury goods company. Arnault and his family have an estimated net worth of US$230 billion as of July 2023, according to Forbes, making him one of the wealthiest people in the world."
